Recipe Sorter

Quick start
1. Create and activate venv (first time only)
  python -m venv .venv
  .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

2. Install dependencies
  pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run the web app
  python app.py

The app will be available at:
http://127.0.0.1:5000

Recipe scanner options

Option A: Scan from the UI
1. Open http://127.0.0.1:5000
2. Enter any username
3. Go to Dashboard
4. Paste a recipe URL in Import a recipe

Option B: Scan from API (PowerShell)
$body = @{ url = "https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/easy-pancakes"; user_id = "test-user" } | ConvertTo-Json
Invoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:5000/recipes/import" -ContentType "application/json" -Body $body

Option C: Scan directly from terminal (no API call required)
python app.py --scan "https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/easy-pancakes"

Useful endpoints
- GET /health
- GET /users/<user_id>/recipes
- GET /recipes/<recipe_id>